# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Remote CLI Configuration
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Override the environment variables in .env for the local CLI environment
# This file enables running the backend-cli locally to manage a remote server

# PURPOSE:
# The backend-cli is designed to run in Docker, but can also be executed locally
# for development and remote server management. When running locally, this file
# provides the necessary configuration to connect to a remote beabee instance.

# LOADING ORDER (when NOT running in Docker):
# 1. .env.remote (this file, when copied)
# 2. .env (root environment file)
# 3. .env.test (if NODE_ENV=test)

# USAGE:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.remote
# 2. Update the configuration values to match your remote server
# 3. Run CLI commands locally: yarn backend-cli [command]

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Remote Database Configuration
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------

# PostgreSQL connection URL for remote database
# Format: postgres://username:password@host:port/database
# This should point to your remote beabee database instance
# Example for local Docker environment (default):
BEABEE_DATABASE_URL=postgres://membership_system:membership_system@localhost:6543/membership_system

# For remote production server, update to something like:
# BEABEE_DATABASE_URL=postgres://username:password@your-server.com:5432/beabee_production

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Additional Remote Configuration
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Add any other environment variables needed to connect to your remote instance
# Examples:
# BEABEE_SECRET=your_remote_secret_key
# BEABEE_AUDIENCE=https://your-beabee-instance.com
# BEABEE_DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:pass@remote-host:5432/beabee
